Finance Minister Kemi Adeosun, has reportedly resigned from the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari.
According to Daily Trust, Adeosun resigned over allegations that she forged her National Youth Service Corps certificate.
A report by the Premium Times about two months ago revealed the minister forged her National Youth Service Corps exemption certificate.
It is taking the presidency months to investigate the allegation which was still on-going as at the time the minister resigned.
